From: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
Subject: kABI: genirq: Delay deactivation in free_irq()
Patch-mainline: never, kabi
References: kabi git-fixes

Commit 4001d8e8762f (genirq: Delay deactivation in free_irq()) added an
include of linux/irqdomain.h into kernel/irq/manage.c. This defined
strict device_node and kabi checker complains about it.

Simply hide the include from the kabi checker.

Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 kernel/irq/manage.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/kernel/irq/manage.c
+++ b/kernel/irq/manage.c
@@ -14,7 +14,9 @@
 #include <linux/module.h>
 #include <linux/random.h>
 #include <linux/interrupt.h>
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
 #include <linux/irqdomain.h>
+#endif
 #include <linux/slab.h>
 #include <linux/sched.h>
 #include <linux/sched/rt.h>
